step-12

Template inheritance
---------------------

create base.html file(skelton file)


blocks : {% block content%} {% endblock %}   ------add this in changes occurring fields.(title,body,..etc) 

Inheritance :{% extends "base.html" %}       ------- using extends every html pages can Inherit base.html file 



------------------------------------------




step-13

how to activate  navbar in base html
---------------------
1-first we have to give the name ='home'  --- in app(home)------urls.py

eg--- path('',views.index,name='home'),
    path('about',views.about,name='about'),
    path('booking',views.booking,name='booking'),


2-second goto base.html and replace href="#"   to -----  {% url 'home'%}
-----------------------
eg-----  <a class="nav-link text-white" href="{% url 'home'%}">Home </a>
            </li>
            <li class="nav-item">
              <a class="nav-link text-white" href="{% url 'about'%}">About</a>
            </li>
            <li class="nav-item">
              <a class="nav-link text-white" href="{% url 'booking'%}">Booking</a>
            </li>

