✅ Day-6 – Final Checklist


Django – Admin, Static Files & Models



📘 Study & Revise Properly

Make sure you understand each step clearly before coming 👇




🔹 Step-14: Django Admin


✔ What is Django Admin
Built-in panel to manage database
Add, update, delete data



✔ Create Superuser
python manage.py createsuperuser





✔ Fix Migration Errors

python manage.py makemigrations
python manage.py migrate





✔ Login to Admin

👉 URL:

http://127.0.0.1:8000/admin

👉 Use superuser credentials







✔ Key Understanding

Admin is used to manage database easily

No need to write UI manually






🔹 Step-15: Static Files


✔ What are Static Files
CSS → styling
JS → functionality
Images → UI


✔ Folder Structure
static/
    css/
    js/
    images/




✔ settings.py Configuration

STATIC_URL = 'static/'


import os

STATICFILES_DIRS = [os.path.join(BASE_DIR, 'static')]





✔ Load Static in Template

{% load static %}

✔ Add CSS

<link rel="stylesheet" href="{% static 'css/style.css' %}">

✔ Add Image

<img src="{% static 'images/car1.jpeg' %}">


✔ Add JavaScript

<script src="{% static 'js/script.js' %}"></script>





✔ Key Understanding

👉 Static files are used for UI design

👉 Must load using {% load static %}








🔹 Step-16: Models (Database)

✔ What is a Model

Represents a table in database





✔ Create Model

from django.db import models

class Departments(models.Model):
    dep_name = models.CharField(max_length=100)
    dep_description = models.TextField()






✔ Register Model in Admin

from .models import Departments

admin.site.register(Departments)







✔ Run Migrations

python manage.py makemigrations

python manage.py migrate







✔ Add Data via Admin

Open admin panel
Add department name & description







✔ Fetch Data in Views

from .models import Departments

def department(request):
    dict_dept = {
        'dept': Departments.objects.all()
    }
    return render(request, 'department.html', dict_dept)





✔ Display Data in Template

{% for d in dept %}

<h1>{{ d.dep_name }}</h1>
<p>{{ d.dep_description }}</p>

{% endfor %}






👉 Admin → manage data
👉 Static → design UI
👉 Model → database table
👉 View → send data
👉 Template → display data



